# Project Cleanup Walkthrough

I have completed the initial cleanup of the Hán-Nôm project. This has removed several gigabytes of logs, caches, and redundant data.

## Architecture Walkthrough Diagram
Đây là biểu đồ quy trình hoạt động của hệ thống Hán-Nôm Heritage Platform:

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "🌐 Client Layer"
        User["Researcher (Browser)"]
    end

    subgraph "🛡️ Proxy Layer (Nginx)"
        Proxy["Nginx (hannom.lyvuha.com)"]
    end

    subgraph "🎨 Frontend Layer (Vite/React)"
        Web["Heritage UI (Port 3000)"]
    end

    subgraph "⚙️ Backend API Layer (FastAPI)"
        API["FastAPI Core (Port 8000)"]
        OCR["OCR Service (YOLO + Qwen2.5)"]
        RAG["RAG Service (LangChain)"]
    end

    subgraph "📂 Data & AI Storage"
        MinIO["MinIO (High-res Images)"]
        Postgres["PostgreSQL (Metadata)"]
        Redis["Redis (Cache)"]
        Milvus["Milvus (Vector Vectors)"]
    end

    User -->|Access| Proxy
    Proxy -->|Root Path /| Web
    Proxy -->|API Path /api/| API
    
    Web -->|Upload Scan| API
    API -->|Save Raw| MinIO
    API -->|Trigger| OCR
    OCR -->|Extract Text| Postgres
    
    API -->|Query context| RAG
    RAG -->|Semantic Search| Milvus
    API -->|Fast Cache| Redis
```

## Actions Completed

### 1. Reclaimed Disk Space
- **~14.2GB Reclaimed Total:** Removed 12.6GB of visualizations from [data/](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Han_Nom_Model/backend/app/models/document.py#20-40) and over 1.5GB of old model versions/logs.
- **Caches Cleared:** Removed `unsloth_compiled_cache/` and Tensorboard `runs/`.

### 2. Smarter Project Structure
I have reorganized the project into a modular hierarchy to make it easier to manage:
- **`scripts/`**: Now organized into `data_prep/`, `training/`, `inference/`, and `tools/`.
- **`assets/`**: Consolidates fonts, dictionaries, and test images.
- **`data/metadata/`**: Stores reference CSVs and analysis results.
- **`models/`**: Centralized location for model weights and architecture code.

### 3. Documentation Update
- **Comprehensive READMEs**: Created README files for all major directories (`scripts/`, `data/`, `assets/`, `models/`, `checkpoints/`) to explain their contents and roles in the pipeline.
- Updated root [README.md](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Han_Nom_Model/README.md) with the new directory map and updated script paths.

### 4. Heritage Platform "First Setup"
I have initialized the full-stack architecture described in your prompt document:
- **Infrastructure Layer**: [docker-compose.yml](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Han_Nom_Model/docker-compose.yml) provides PostgreSQL, MinIO, Redis, and Milvus.
- **Backend (FastAPI)**: Modular API architecture in `backend/` ready for OCR and Dictionary integration.
- **Frontend (React/Vite)**: A premium, dark-themed UI in `frontend/` powered by Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, and Lucide React.
- **Initialization**: Created a [setup.sh](file:///home/alida/Documents/Cursor/Han_Nom_Model/setup.sh) script to streamline the installation of all dependencies.

### 5. Custom Domain & Reverse Proxy
The platform is now optimized for use with your custom domain **`hannom.lyvuha.com`**:
- **Nginx Reverse Proxy**: Automatically routes `/api/` traffic to the backend and all other traffic to the frontend.
- **CORS Configuration**: Backend is securely configured to allow cross-origin requests from your production domain.
- **Dynamic API Routing**: Frontend uses relative paths to ensure seamless communication regardless of the environment.

## Reclaimed Space Summary
- **Total Reclaimed: 14.2 GB**
- **Kept: 17 GB `raw` data** as requested.

